    "client_msg_id": "2894d5a6-b886-4e70-a0d5-88529a1af6b1",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "[moved from top level, original post by <@U01U19ECZTJ>]\n\n1. Yes gain access to the database. 2. Yes, the audit log is the database, like a blockchain. You can't fudge with the audit logs because they're cryptographically hashed. On a restart the server would detect the tampering and refuse to load or startup. This also lets us run our filesystem in append-only mode. Also, the data is not actually stored on the server, but is instead stored in separate append-only MEDUSA nodes. Each audit entry is actually in two blockchains, one specific to the MEDUSA node and the global chain (which is actually a DAG). You would need access to all of the MEDUSA nodes and be able to fake the signatures/hashes.\n",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1617911071.074600",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
