          {
            "type": "rich_text_list",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "rich_text_section",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Yes gain access to the database. 2. Yes, the audit log is the database, like a blockchain. You can't fudge with the audit logs because they're cryptographically hashed. On a restart the server would detect the tampering and refuse to load or startup. This also lets us run our filesystem in append-only mode. Also, the data is not actually stored on the server, but is instead stored in separate append-only MEDUSA nodes. Each audit entry is actually in two blockchains, one specific to the MEDUSA node and the global chain (which is actually a DAG). You would need access to all of the MEDUSA nodes and be able to fake the signatures/hashes."
                  }
